1
00:00:11,428 --> 00:00:16,433
[CROWD cheering]

2
00:00:16,475 --> 00:00:18,936
[HOST GOD] Now!
Assembled gods and goddesses,

3
00:00:18,977 --> 00:00:21,063
may I have your
attention, please!

4
00:00:21,104 --> 00:00:22,981
The difficulty level
for this next salvation

5
00:00:23,023 --> 00:00:24,775
will be the dreaded S‐Class!

6
00:00:24,816 --> 00:00:27,819
And doing the honors
this time will be...

7
00:00:29,780 --> 00:00:32,658
[HOST GOD]
...The Goddess Ristarte!

8
00:00:32,699 --> 00:00:34,409
[GODDESS 01A]
I'm so glad it's you, Rista!

9
00:00:34,451 --> 00:00:35,953
[GOD 01A] You have some
big tasks ahead of you.

10
00:00:35,994 --> 00:00:37,079
[GODDESS 01B]
Once you finish this,

11
00:00:37,120 --> 00:00:39,456
you'll be a full‐fledged,
legitimate goddess!

12
00:00:39,498 --> 00:00:42,918
Thank you, all. I vow to use
this endeavor to better myself

13
00:00:42,960 --> 00:00:43,919
and gain experience

14
00:00:43,961 --> 00:00:46,380
so I can one day become
a high‐ranking goddess!

15
00:00:46,421 --> 00:00:49,550
Are you freakin' kidding me?!

16
00:00:51,677 --> 00:00:53,762
[panting]

17
00:00:53,804 --> 00:00:57,766
Ugh, I can't believe they
gave me an S‐Class job!

18
00:00:57,808 --> 00:01:00,185
[RISTA] I'm Ristarte,
or "Rista," for short.

19
00:01:00,227 --> 00:01:02,604
I was born into the
Unified Divine Realm,

20
00:01:02,646 --> 00:01:05,232
let's just say, 100 years ago.

21
00:01:05,274 --> 00:01:07,150
I've summoned heroes
from the human realm

22
00:01:07,192 --> 00:01:10,571
to save worlds on the brink
of collapse five times so far.

23
00:01:11,572 --> 00:01:14,533
[RISTA] But compared to the
higher level gods and goddesses,

24
00:01:14,575 --> 00:01:16,577
five times is
nothing to brag about.

25
00:01:16,618 --> 00:01:19,830
The average is about ten,
and some of the big deal deities

26
00:01:19,871 --> 00:01:23,000
have saved hundreds of worlds.

27
00:01:23,041 --> 00:01:24,293
And in case you're wondering,

28
00:01:24,334 --> 00:01:27,421
S‐Class means that the world
is so messed up and dangerous,

29
00:01:27,462 --> 00:01:31,174
that even the most experienced
gods don't wanna go near it.

30
00:01:31,216 --> 00:01:34,678
[RISTA whimpering]

31
00:01:38,640 --> 00:01:39,766
[RISTA]
The last few times,

32
00:01:39,808 --> 00:01:42,311
I've chosen a young man from
Japan to summon as the hero.

33
00:01:42,352 --> 00:01:44,187
They seem the easiest to train.

34
00:01:44,229 --> 00:01:45,897
Japan has a lot of
stories about people

35
00:01:45,939 --> 00:01:48,734
being taken to another
world for various reasons,

36
00:01:48,775 --> 00:01:50,694
so they get the idea
pretty quickly.

37
00:01:50,736 --> 00:01:52,738
And though the public is on
the verge of being completely

38
00:01:52,779 --> 00:01:54,531
oversaturated with
this kind of story,

39
00:01:54,573 --> 00:01:56,992
the sheer number of them can
only mean it's still popular.

40
00:01:57,034 --> 00:01:58,702
Wait, why am I narrating?

41
00:01:58,744 --> 00:01:59,745
[groans]

42
00:01:59,786 --> 00:02:02,497
I'm so stressed,
I'm losing my mind.

43
00:02:02,539 --> 00:02:06,793
I can only summon one hero,
so I have to choose carefully.

44
00:02:06,835 --> 00:02:08,545
Suzuki...

45
00:02:08,587 --> 00:02:10,005
Sasaki...

46
00:02:10,047 --> 00:02:12,466
Suzuki, Yamada.

47
00:02:12,507 --> 00:02:14,217
Sasaki, Sato.

48
00:02:14,259 --> 00:02:17,137
Suzuki, Tanaka, Sasaki,
Yamada, Sasaki, Suzuki,

49
00:02:17,179 --> 00:02:19,181
Yamada, Yamada, Tanaka,
Yamada, Sasaki, Suzuki.

50
00:02:19,222 --> 00:02:23,060
[RISTA yells]
Jeez! They all look alike to me!

51
00:02:24,519 --> 00:02:25,646
[RISTA yells]

52
00:02:25,687 --> 00:02:28,190
I need to make some
kind of decision here!

53
00:02:28,231 --> 00:02:30,108
[gasps, yelps]

54
00:02:30,150 --> 00:02:32,527
[RISTA groans]

55
00:02:38,492 --> 00:02:41,828
[RISTA grunting]

56
00:02:41,870 --> 00:02:43,288
Stupid paperwork!

57
00:02:43,330 --> 00:02:46,249
Uh... Huh? Huh? Huh?!

58
00:02:46,291 --> 00:02:48,710
Hold on just a minute!
This guy is a level one,

59
00:02:48,752 --> 00:02:51,213
but his stats are
unbelievably high!

60
00:02:54,549 --> 00:02:58,011
Wow. I've never seen a human
with numbers like these before!

61
00:02:58,053 --> 00:02:58,929
Oh, yes!

62
00:02:58,970 --> 00:03:01,306
Whoever this is,
he's a total phenom!

63
00:03:01,348 --> 00:03:03,517
A one in a million
find for sure!

64
00:03:03,558 --> 00:03:07,646
No, he's more like a one
in a hundred million find!

65
00:03:07,688 --> 00:03:09,022
[RISTA]
He'll be able get Gaeabrande

66
00:03:09,064 --> 00:03:10,565
back in order in no time!

67
00:03:10,607 --> 00:03:12,150
And I'll be that
much closer to being

68
00:03:12,192 --> 00:03:14,152
a super high‐ranking goddess!

69
00:03:14,194 --> 00:03:15,696
Heh! Yeah!

70
00:03:15,737 --> 00:03:18,740
I'm the luckiest
goddess there ever was!

71
00:03:18,782 --> 00:03:20,242
[RISTA chuckles]

72
00:03:27,499 --> 00:03:28,875
[RISTA]
Hmm.

73
00:03:34,172 --> 00:03:36,883
By the power of
the goddess Ristarte,

74
00:03:36,925 --> 00:03:40,053
I now summon a hero
to this sacred chamber.

75
00:03:43,306 --> 00:03:46,560
Come forth, Seiya Ryuuguuin!

76
00:03:54,443 --> 00:03:56,278
[gasps]

77
00:04:06,538 --> 00:04:08,498
[RISTA]
Wow, he's dreamy!

78
00:04:08,540 --> 00:04:09,499
He's six feet tall,

79
00:04:09,541 --> 00:04:12,210
with noble features under
that luscious dark hair.

80
00:04:12,252 --> 00:04:13,879
And he gives off
an aura that's as heavenly

81
00:04:13,920 --> 00:04:16,965
as the Great Gods in
the Unified Divine Realm.

82
00:04:17,007 --> 00:04:18,049
Oh, I could lose myself

83
00:04:18,091 --> 00:04:20,010
in passionate love
with a man like this!

84
00:04:20,051 --> 00:04:22,971
Wait! A goddess getting
involved in a steamy romance

85
00:04:23,013 --> 00:04:25,140
with a human is uber forbidden!

86
00:04:26,183 --> 00:04:27,476
Ehem.

87
00:04:27,517 --> 00:04:30,187
Greetings, I am the goddess
known as Ristarte.

88
00:04:30,228 --> 00:04:31,897
I know this must
be quite shocking,

89
00:04:31,938 --> 00:04:33,648
but it is out of
urgent necessity that

90
00:04:33,690 --> 00:04:36,526
I have summoned you from the
human world into our dimension.

91
00:04:36,568 --> 00:04:39,279
Hearken to my words
carefully, Seiya Ryuuguuin,

92
00:04:39,321 --> 00:04:41,406
for you are the hero
chosen to save the world

93
00:04:41,448 --> 00:04:44,242
of Gaeabrande
from the Demon Lord.

94
00:04:44,284 --> 00:04:45,410
[RISTA chuckles]

95
00:04:45,452 --> 00:04:47,871
[RISTA] He's so enchanted by
me that he can't even speak.

96
00:04:47,913 --> 00:04:50,207
But I mean, who could blame him?
I am a goddess after all.

97
00:04:50,248 --> 00:04:52,250
And not to be vain, but I
know I've got it goin' on‐‐

98
00:04:52,292 --> 00:04:54,503
What kinda freak drops a bomb
like this on a stranger?

99
00:04:54,544 --> 00:04:56,880
Who's a freak?!
Are you talking about me?!

100
00:04:56,922 --> 00:04:58,965
[RISTA gasps]
Whoops! Calm down, Rista!

101
00:04:59,007 --> 00:05:00,801
A goddess must always
maintain her composure.

102
00:05:00,842 --> 00:05:04,471
Ehem! I'm sure that you
must be mystified by me.

103
00:05:04,513 --> 00:05:06,473
You've likely never been
in the presence of a goddess

104
00:05:06,515 --> 00:05:08,308
such as me or summoned
to a higher plane

105
00:05:08,350 --> 00:05:09,601
for a task such as this.

106
00:05:09,643 --> 00:05:11,478
If you're really a goddess,
couldn't you just save

107
00:05:11,520 --> 00:05:13,897
whatever‐the‐hell world
it was by yourself?

108
00:05:13,939 --> 00:05:16,525
Well, there are rules in place.

109
00:05:16,566 --> 00:05:18,777
The gods have created
countless worlds

110
00:05:18,819 --> 00:05:21,321
where the humans are
to prosper by their own efforts.

111
00:05:21,363 --> 00:05:23,573
This also means that these
worlds where humans dwell

112
00:05:23,615 --> 00:05:26,576
must be saved by
humans themselves.

113
00:05:26,618 --> 00:05:27,828
What if I refuse?

114
00:05:27,869 --> 00:05:29,204
This is a sacred duty.

115
00:05:29,246 --> 00:05:31,414
‐‐I can't do as I please?
‐‐Not really.

116
00:05:31,456 --> 00:05:32,958
Can I ask you to
change the rules?

117
00:05:32,999 --> 00:05:34,626
No, you cannot!

118
00:05:34,668 --> 00:05:36,711
In other words, you're
just using me. Lame.

119
00:05:36,753 --> 00:05:38,630
This is gonna get old.

120
00:05:38,672 --> 00:05:40,507
[RISTA]
Now, now, he's overwhelmed,

121
00:05:40,549 --> 00:05:42,217
so take it easy on him.

122
00:05:42,259 --> 00:05:43,635
It seems like most
of these guys perk up

123
00:05:43,677 --> 00:05:44,970
when I start the next part.

124
00:05:45,011 --> 00:05:47,973
Hey, how about you try
calling out "Status"?

125
00:05:48,014 --> 00:05:49,224
‐‐Why?
‐‐Sorry.

126
00:05:49,266 --> 00:05:52,853
I suppose I just assumed that
you were a gamer. I'll explain.

127
00:05:52,894 --> 00:05:54,646
When you call out
"Status," your abilities

128
00:05:54,688 --> 00:05:57,649
will magically appear before
you in glowing numeric form.

129
00:05:57,691 --> 00:05:58,984
Go on, give it a whirl!

130
00:05:59,025 --> 00:06:00,527
[SEIYA sighs]

131
00:06:00,569 --> 00:06:01,653
Properties.

132
00:06:01,695 --> 00:06:02,988
"Properties"?!

133
00:06:03,029 --> 00:06:04,990
No, we need you to
say "Status," please!

134
00:06:05,031 --> 00:06:06,408
Why would you say
something else?

135
00:06:06,449 --> 00:06:08,201
Does that actually
have meaning, or...?

136
00:06:08,243 --> 00:06:11,246
[SEIYA] Sure enough, I see
some data only I'd know about.

137
00:06:11,288 --> 00:06:13,206
Which means that
your ridiculous story

138
00:06:13,248 --> 00:06:14,749
may have a tiny
shred of credibility.

139
00:06:14,791 --> 00:06:17,752
Ugh! You shouldn't be so
rude to a goddess, ya know?

140
00:06:17,794 --> 00:06:20,171
"Status"! Just say
"Status" already!

141
00:06:20,213 --> 00:06:23,425
Oh, please don't make
me beg you to do it!

142
00:06:23,466 --> 00:06:24,926
All right, Status.

143
00:06:25,927 --> 00:06:27,220
You see all that?

144
00:06:27,262 --> 00:06:30,599
Your stat numbers are above and
beyond any run‐of‐the‐mill hero.

145
00:06:30,640 --> 00:06:33,393
You're a one in a hundred
million phenomenon!

146
00:06:33,435 --> 00:06:34,436
There's only one hero

147
00:06:34,477 --> 00:06:36,730
who can defeat the
Demon Lord of Gaeabrande!

148
00:06:36,771 --> 00:06:40,442
And that hero is you, Seiya!

149
00:06:40,483 --> 00:06:43,528
Ya wanna tell me what happens
if I die in this world?

150
00:06:43,570 --> 00:06:44,905
[RISTA]
What a wet blanket.

151
00:06:44,946 --> 00:06:47,949
Not to worry! You won't be
able to return to Gaeabrande.

152
00:06:47,991 --> 00:06:49,743
You'll just be taken
back to your world.

153
00:06:49,784 --> 00:06:51,202
Huh. Not sold yet.

154
00:06:51,244 --> 00:06:53,997
[RISTA] Ugh. He sure is
a tough nut to crack.

155
00:06:54,039 --> 00:06:56,041
Maybe he has to see it
for it to sink in.

156
00:06:56,082 --> 00:06:57,542
In that case...

157
00:06:57,584 --> 00:07:00,629
[RISTA] Seiya, I'll explain
everything in due time.

158
00:07:00,670 --> 00:07:03,048
Open doorway to the other world!

159
00:07:04,090 --> 00:07:07,427
[RISTA] Come, Seiya Ryuuguuin!
Take my hand and follow me.

160
00:07:07,469 --> 00:07:09,095
The fate of Gaeabrande hinges

161
00:07:09,137 --> 00:07:10,931
on your spectacular
heroic abilities!

162
00:07:10,972 --> 00:07:12,599
‐‐No, thanks.
‐‐This will be an exciting

163
00:07:12,641 --> 00:07:15,393
journey, full of wonders
and feats of‐‐ Uh, wha...?

164
00:07:15,435 --> 00:07:16,311
Did you say no?

165
00:07:16,353 --> 00:07:17,520
[SEIYA]
Of course I said no.

166
00:07:17,562 --> 00:07:20,732
You expect me to just rush
into a fight with a demon?

167
00:07:20,774 --> 00:07:21,608
[RISTA]
Hold on a second!

168
00:07:21,650 --> 00:07:23,902
I would've never chosen you
if you didn't have a chance,

169
00:07:23,944 --> 00:07:26,571
and I can provide backup
whenever you need me to.

170
00:07:26,613 --> 00:07:27,489
So you needn't worry.

171
00:07:27,530 --> 00:07:29,616
I don't believe I can
depend on your backup.

172
00:07:29,658 --> 00:07:32,035
Have you totally forgotten
you're talking to a goddess?

173
00:07:32,077 --> 00:07:33,954
I assure you that I will
not let you die and

174
00:07:33,995 --> 00:07:34,871
if you were to get injured,

175
00:07:34,913 --> 00:07:36,665
I can use my healing
magic on you.

176
00:07:36,706 --> 00:07:39,250
That's not backup and it's
obvious you called me here

177
00:07:39,292 --> 00:07:41,211
because you can't
pull it off yourself.

178
00:07:41,252 --> 00:07:43,338
[RISTA growls]
What is his deal?

179
00:07:43,380 --> 00:07:45,382
I should bash in his
beautiful, brooding face!

180
00:07:45,423 --> 00:07:46,341
[yelps]

181
00:07:46,383 --> 00:07:47,968
[SEIYA]
Listen up. If I can't refuse,

182
00:07:48,009 --> 00:07:50,178
I gotta insist on one condition.

183
00:07:50,220 --> 00:07:53,264
Well, what is it?
What do you want in return?

184
00:07:54,391 --> 00:07:56,518
[gasps]

185
00:07:56,559 --> 00:07:59,270
You mean...? Ah, we mustn't!

186
00:07:59,312 --> 00:08:00,397
[RISTA squeals]

187
00:08:00,438 --> 00:08:02,148
I truly hate to
break your heart,

188
00:08:02,190 --> 00:08:04,859
but love between gods
and mortals is‐‐uh?

189
00:08:04,901 --> 00:08:07,862
If I'm gonna do this, at least
let me get prepared for it.

190
00:08:07,904 --> 00:08:11,032
I need to be 100 percent ready.

191
00:08:11,074 --> 00:08:13,576
Ugh, what kind of hero is he?

192
00:08:13,618 --> 00:08:17,080
[RISTA gasps] Then, like a
bolt of lightning, it hit me.

193
00:08:17,122 --> 00:08:20,291
I had overlooked
a crucial personality trait.

194
00:08:23,336 --> 00:08:27,882
[SEIYA grunting]

195
00:10:00,391 --> 00:10:03,228
I never imagined that
someone like this existed!

196
00:10:03,269 --> 00:10:06,314
Well, how were things
resolved in the end?

197
00:10:06,356 --> 00:10:10,151
[RISTA] He's still training for
it in an empty room at my place.

198
00:10:10,193 --> 00:10:11,736
A normal person
would wanna rush over

199
00:10:11,778 --> 00:10:14,447
and at least see
another world, right?

200
00:10:14,489 --> 00:10:17,617
Rista, your goal is to take
control of Gaeabrande,

201
00:10:17,659 --> 00:10:19,369
which is an S‐Class mission.

202
00:10:19,410 --> 00:10:21,454
Perhaps a cautious attitude
is most appropriate here.

203
00:10:21,496 --> 00:10:24,124
[RISTA groans] But it's
such a colossal waste of time

204
00:10:24,165 --> 00:10:26,668
compared to going there and
fighting some low‐tier monsters

205
00:10:26,709 --> 00:10:28,962
so he can start to
get his XP level up.

206
00:10:29,003 --> 00:10:30,463
I promise it's okay.

207
00:10:30,505 --> 00:10:32,465
You don't need to
be in such a rush.

208
00:10:32,507 --> 00:10:34,634
The flow of time
is considerably slower

209
00:10:34,676 --> 00:10:37,470
in the Divine Realm than it
is in the terrestrial worlds.

210
00:10:37,512 --> 00:10:40,306
I know, but it's just that
I want this adventure

211
00:10:40,348 --> 00:10:42,267
to work the way
that it's supposed to.

212
00:10:42,308 --> 00:10:45,478
No matter your expectations,
he still needs your support.

213
00:10:45,520 --> 00:10:47,647
Which in this case means
if he's busy training,

214
00:10:47,689 --> 00:10:49,649
you need to be
looking after him.

215
00:10:49,691 --> 00:10:50,817
[RISTA]
What do you mean by that?

216
00:10:50,859 --> 00:10:52,944
Like, how are his
living conditions?

217
00:10:52,986 --> 00:10:55,238
Does he have a toilet
and place to shower?

218
00:10:55,280 --> 00:10:56,114
Does he have a bed?

219
00:10:56,156 --> 00:10:57,407
[RISTA grunts]

220
00:10:57,448 --> 00:10:59,117
[ARIA]
What have you given him to eat?

221
00:10:59,159 --> 00:11:00,702
[gasps]

222
00:11:00,743 --> 00:11:02,453
[RISTA]
Now that you mention it...

223
00:11:02,495 --> 00:11:03,955
And be sure to keep in mind‐‐

224
00:11:03,997 --> 00:11:06,332
if you're giving him orders and
reminding him you're a goddess,

225
00:11:06,374 --> 00:11:07,959
he may not respond that well.

226
00:11:08,001 --> 00:11:11,212
He might be more agreeable
if you treated him as a friend.

227
00:11:11,254 --> 00:11:13,089
You're right, as always, Aria!

228
00:11:13,131 --> 00:11:15,133
I knew I could count on you!

229
00:11:16,217 --> 00:11:18,803
Another pep talk
right on schedule.

230
00:11:22,557 --> 00:11:25,602
[RISTA] Hey! I'm so sorry for
leaving you here all by your‐‐

231
00:11:25,643 --> 00:11:27,395
[RISTA]
Holy six‐pack!

232
00:11:27,437 --> 00:11:30,523
[SEIYA] Yo, does the concept of
knocking not exist here or what?

233
00:11:30,565 --> 00:11:32,108
Oh, whoops.

234
00:11:32,150 --> 00:11:34,861
[RISTA] Wait a minute,
this is my place after all.

235
00:11:34,903 --> 00:11:36,237
[RISTA]
I bet you're hungry!

236
00:11:36,279 --> 00:11:37,238
What's that?

237
00:11:37,280 --> 00:11:38,489
[RISTA]
Well, since you're Japanese,

238
00:11:38,531 --> 00:11:40,158
I brought you some rice balls.

239
00:11:40,200 --> 00:11:42,827
This one is pickled plum and
this one has some yummy salmon!

240
00:11:42,869 --> 00:11:44,329
[SEIYA]
Hmm. I was raised to never

241
00:11:44,370 --> 00:11:46,372
accept food from
weird strangers.

242
00:11:46,414 --> 00:11:49,250
I am not a stranger,
so would ya stop being so rude?

243
00:11:49,292 --> 00:11:50,919
‐‐You should eat it first.
‐‐Why?!

244
00:11:50,960 --> 00:11:53,046
I need to be sure that
it's not poisoned.

245
00:11:53,087 --> 00:11:56,216
What reason would
I have to poison you?

246
00:11:56,257 --> 00:11:58,176
You see? It's just fine.

247
00:11:58,218 --> 00:12:00,053
Why in the realm would
I try to kill you?

248
00:12:00,094 --> 00:12:03,264
Okay, so there's no fast‐acting
poison in them. Huh.

249
00:12:03,306 --> 00:12:05,683
No slow‐acting poison, either!

250
00:12:09,896 --> 00:12:11,397
[RISTA]
Oh, and FYI,

251
00:12:11,439 --> 00:12:13,024
push‐ups, pull‐ups, and sit‐ups

252
00:12:13,066 --> 00:12:15,360
don't do anything
to increase your stats.

253
00:12:15,401 --> 00:12:17,320
I'll leave three meals
a day outside your door,

254
00:12:17,362 --> 00:12:18,446
but I won't bother you.

255
00:12:18,488 --> 00:12:20,990
When you're finally ready,
you can call me with this!

256
00:12:21,032 --> 00:12:21,991
Until you call me,

257
00:12:22,033 --> 00:12:24,994
I promise to leave you in
complete solitude, okay?

258
00:12:25,036 --> 00:12:27,413
What? Is that not
enough for you?

259
00:12:27,455 --> 00:12:29,874
How do I know that this
won't trigger an explosive?

260
00:12:29,916 --> 00:12:32,126
‐‐Say wha...?
‐‐[door closes]

261
00:12:32,168 --> 00:12:34,337
Well, he can do whatever
he pleases in there!

262
00:12:34,379 --> 00:12:37,507
I give it three days tops
before he buzzes me!

263
00:12:37,548 --> 00:12:41,427
Still no buzz. Is it broken?

264
00:12:41,469 --> 00:12:43,763
Or did something else happen?

265
00:12:43,805 --> 00:12:46,015
It could be bad.

266
00:12:46,057 --> 00:12:47,350
He's dead?!

267
00:12:48,434 --> 00:12:51,062
But he is eating
the food I leave him.

268
00:12:52,814 --> 00:12:54,983
I guess I'll just
keep on waiting.

269
00:12:55,024 --> 00:12:58,403
[RISTA groans]
It's never gonna ring.

270
00:12:58,444 --> 00:13:00,697
I'll have to wait forever.

271
00:13:00,738 --> 00:13:03,783
[RISTA DOLL ringing]

272
00:13:03,825 --> 00:13:06,577
[RISTA]
You rang? Oh!

273
00:13:10,039 --> 00:13:12,750
[RISTA]
Sexy... So fresh and so clean.

274
00:13:12,792 --> 00:13:14,752
I remember telling
you to knock first.

275
00:13:14,794 --> 00:13:16,296
Yeah, I'm the rude one here.

276
00:13:16,337 --> 00:13:18,047
So how's the training going?

277
00:13:18,089 --> 00:13:19,215
[SEIYA]
Status.

278
00:13:20,216 --> 00:13:22,260
[RISTA]
Hmm.

279
00:13:22,302 --> 00:13:23,303
[RISTA gasps]

280
00:13:23,344 --> 00:13:26,264
[RISTA] You leveled up like
crazy just from working out?!

281
00:13:26,306 --> 00:13:29,142
You do have that unique
"XP boost" skill, after all.

282
00:13:29,183 --> 00:13:30,768
And now you have
other special skills?

283
00:13:30,810 --> 00:13:32,186
If it were completely up to me,

284
00:13:32,228 --> 00:13:34,230
I'd like to max out
my levels first.

285
00:13:34,272 --> 00:13:36,441
You'd spend the rest
of your life in here!

286
00:13:36,482 --> 00:13:37,942
Time passes slowly
in this realm,

287
00:13:37,984 --> 00:13:39,360
but we don't have forever!

288
00:13:39,402 --> 00:13:41,863
We have to get going.

289
00:13:41,904 --> 00:13:43,489
On to Gaeabrande!

290
00:13:43,531 --> 00:13:44,824
[SEIYA]
Yeah, okay.

291
00:13:46,951 --> 00:13:49,078
I am perfectly prepared.

292
00:13:49,120 --> 00:13:51,205
I am 100 percent ready for this.

293
00:13:51,247 --> 00:13:52,665
[RISTA]
What is he doing?

294
00:13:52,707 --> 00:13:54,709
Trying to work in some
cool little catchphrase?

295
00:13:54,751 --> 00:13:56,711
[RISTA] Great! But you
don't have to say that.

296
00:13:56,753 --> 00:13:58,338
Let's just go, already!

297
00:14:05,303 --> 00:14:07,138
The Great Goddess
Ishtar determined

298
00:14:07,180 --> 00:14:10,058
this was the perfect place
for us to enter this world.

299
00:14:10,099 --> 00:14:12,268
Now, we need to go
into the Town of Edona

300
00:14:12,310 --> 00:14:13,770
and get your equipment.

301
00:14:25,990 --> 00:14:28,368
Hello. You just passing through?

302
00:14:28,409 --> 00:14:30,036
Hello! Yes, we are.

303
00:14:30,078 --> 00:14:32,372
Are you sure it's safe
to be casually walking

304
00:14:32,413 --> 00:14:35,249
around this strange village when
you're dressed like a stripper?

305
00:14:35,291 --> 00:14:36,834
Watch your mouth, pal!

306
00:14:36,876 --> 00:14:38,336
And I used my goddess power

307
00:14:38,378 --> 00:14:40,755
to make it look like
I'm wearing normal clothes!

308
00:14:40,797 --> 00:14:42,131
I'm not nearly as concerned

309
00:14:42,173 --> 00:14:44,759
about your outfit as
I am about that man.

310
00:14:44,801 --> 00:14:46,844
He could well be
a monster in disguise.

311
00:14:46,886 --> 00:14:49,013
Jeez, he's just a regular guy.

312
00:14:49,055 --> 00:14:50,681
I don't like the look of him.

313
00:14:50,723 --> 00:14:52,433
It's possible he's
a shapeshifter.

314
00:14:52,475 --> 00:14:53,976
[RISTA]
No, it's not.

315
00:14:54,018 --> 00:14:55,645
[SEIYA] Even if he's
not literally a monster,

316
00:14:55,686 --> 00:14:57,814
he could be a thief,
or a mass murderer.

317
00:14:57,855 --> 00:15:01,067
I may need to take him
out before he kills us.

318
00:15:01,109 --> 00:15:03,945
You're the one who sounds like
a murderer, you paranoid weirdo!

319
00:15:03,986 --> 00:15:07,281
Oh, wow, you sure look super
pretty in that outfit, lady!

320
00:15:07,323 --> 00:15:09,534
You're like a goddess
or somethin'!

321
00:15:10,618 --> 00:15:11,661
How sweet.

322
00:15:11,702 --> 00:15:14,539
Innocent little children can
always recognize true beauty.

323
00:15:14,580 --> 00:15:17,166
[NINA giggles] Mister,
you got some funny clothes,

324
00:15:17,208 --> 00:15:19,085
but you seem really cool anyway!

325
00:15:19,127 --> 00:15:22,088
My, are you gonna let some
childish remark upset you?

326
00:15:22,130 --> 00:15:24,507
I bet they call you Mister Cool!

327
00:15:24,549 --> 00:15:26,134
What's your real name?

328
00:15:27,218 --> 00:15:28,219
It's Seiya.

329
00:15:28,261 --> 00:15:31,180
Ooh, my name's Nina!
Nice to meet you!

330
00:15:31,222 --> 00:15:33,141
I'd love to watch this
interaction go on,

331
00:15:33,182 --> 00:15:34,767
but we have a job to do.

332
00:15:34,809 --> 00:15:36,310
Oh, tell me, Nina.

333
00:15:36,352 --> 00:15:38,646
Is there a blacksmith
or weapons shop nearby?

334
00:15:38,688 --> 00:15:40,898
Yeah, there's a place
like that real close.

335
00:15:40,940 --> 00:15:43,693
Just a little bit down
the road that way.

336
00:15:43,734 --> 00:15:46,070
[RISTA]
Thanks, Nina. I appreciate it!

337
00:15:48,698 --> 00:15:50,867
Here's a little
present from me to you.

338
00:15:50,908 --> 00:15:52,243
This should be more
than enough money

339
00:15:52,285 --> 00:15:54,579
to buy whatever you
think you're gonna need.

340
00:15:56,164 --> 00:15:57,498
[WEAPONS SHOP OWNER]
Welcome.

341
00:16:00,001 --> 00:16:02,336
Definitely gonna take this
steel armor right here.

342
00:16:02,378 --> 00:16:04,005
[RISTA]
Nice, excellent choice!

343
00:16:04,046 --> 00:16:04,964
Three sets.

344
00:16:05,006 --> 00:16:06,507
Not so fast!

345
00:16:06,549 --> 00:16:08,509
You don't need that much armor!

346
00:16:08,551 --> 00:16:10,511
[SEIYA]
I do because I need one to wear,

347
00:16:10,553 --> 00:16:13,306
one for spare, and one more
in case the spare needs a spare.

348
00:16:13,347 --> 00:16:15,224
[RISTA]
Do you have an armor fetish?

349
00:16:15,266 --> 00:16:16,851
What kind of
ridiculous hero spends

350
00:16:16,893 --> 00:16:19,270
all his money on three
identical sets of armor?

351
00:16:19,312 --> 00:16:21,856
I'll choose one for you,
so just stay put, okay?

352
00:16:21,898 --> 00:16:23,357
You're not the boss of me.

353
00:16:23,399 --> 00:16:26,944
[RISTA] He's not just
cautious, he's pathological.

354
00:16:32,283 --> 00:16:33,910
[RISTA]
Mm, that's way better.

355
00:16:33,951 --> 00:16:36,704
You really look like
the ideal hero to me!

356
00:16:36,746 --> 00:16:38,498
[bell chimes]

357
00:16:38,539 --> 00:16:39,790
[SEIYA]
I need 30 smoke bombs,

358
00:16:39,832 --> 00:16:43,002
50 medicinal herbs,
and 50 antidotal herbs.

359
00:16:43,044 --> 00:16:45,004
[ITEM SHOP OWNER]
Oh, yes, coming right up, sir.

360
00:16:45,046 --> 00:16:46,214
Thank you!

361
00:16:46,255 --> 00:16:48,257
[RISTA] At least they're
not that expensive.

362
00:16:48,299 --> 00:16:50,593
But still, you bought so many!

363
00:16:50,635 --> 00:16:53,095
[SEIYA] There's no telling
what we might encounter,

364
00:16:53,137 --> 00:16:54,472
so I need to be prepared.

365
00:16:54,514 --> 00:16:57,767
I may not look it, but I am
a veteran at this stuff.

366
00:16:57,808 --> 00:17:01,187
Therefore, I located the
perfect starting place for you.

367
00:17:01,229 --> 00:17:03,564
There's nothing but
weak monsters around here.

368
00:17:03,606 --> 00:17:04,565
I'm not so sure,

369
00:17:04,607 --> 00:17:06,943
and I highly doubt you're
a veteran, like you claim.

370
00:17:06,984 --> 00:17:08,694
[RISTA]
Why would I be lying?!

371
00:17:08,736 --> 00:17:10,488
[NINA]
She's right!

372
00:17:10,530 --> 00:17:11,531
It's true!

373
00:17:11,572 --> 00:17:15,493
Even I can walk over to the next
town with no problem at all!

374
00:17:15,535 --> 00:17:16,702
Only things we gotta deal with

375
00:17:16,744 --> 00:17:18,746
are wibbly, wobbly
little slimes!

376
00:17:18,788 --> 00:17:21,749
If a cute little girl can
handle it, then so can you!

377
00:17:21,791 --> 00:17:23,584
Does that put your mind at ease?

378
00:17:23,626 --> 00:17:25,127
You look pretty
strong, Mr. Seiya.

379
00:17:25,169 --> 00:17:27,255
Are you really afraid
of going outside of town?

380
00:17:27,296 --> 00:17:28,673
Yeah, underneath all that armor,

381
00:17:28,714 --> 00:17:31,050
he's actually just a big,
strong, fraidy‐cat!

382
00:17:31,092 --> 00:17:33,010
Well, then, take this!

383
00:17:33,052 --> 00:17:36,055
This charm will
ward off any evil.

384
00:17:38,182 --> 00:17:39,976
You didn't put a curse
on this, did you?

385
00:17:40,017 --> 00:17:41,769
[RISTA]
Jeez! Just stop it!

386
00:17:41,811 --> 00:17:42,645
What'd you say?

387
00:17:42,687 --> 00:17:45,565
Don't pay any attention to him,
he's just a little sick!

388
00:17:45,606 --> 00:17:47,275
Nina, what've you got into?

389
00:17:47,316 --> 00:17:49,235
Hey! Papa!

390
00:17:49,277 --> 00:17:50,736
[TOYA]
I apologize.

391
00:17:50,778 --> 00:17:52,363
My daughter can
be a little nosy.

392
00:17:52,405 --> 00:17:53,614
I'm sorry if she bothered you.

393
00:17:53,656 --> 00:17:55,741
[RISTA]
No, no, not at all!

394
00:17:55,783 --> 00:17:56,826
Right?

395
00:17:56,867 --> 00:17:59,161
No, not very much, at least.

396
00:17:59,203 --> 00:18:03,165
[RISTA] Hmm. So he's not
completely disagreeable.

397
00:18:03,207 --> 00:18:06,168
[RISTA] Okay, it's finally
monster fight o'clock!

398
00:18:06,210 --> 00:18:07,587
I don't see any good reason

399
00:18:07,628 --> 00:18:09,672
why we need to go out
looking for trouble.

400
00:18:09,714 --> 00:18:11,507
[RISTA]
Don't be such a diaper baby.

401
00:18:11,549 --> 00:18:14,010
You have enough gear
to take on an army!

402
00:18:15,720 --> 00:18:17,430
There's a little monster!

403
00:18:17,471 --> 00:18:19,557
I've never seen
anything like that before.

404
00:18:19,599 --> 00:18:21,475
Are they genetically engineered?

405
00:18:21,517 --> 00:18:23,102
Don't you know what a slime is?

406
00:18:23,144 --> 00:18:24,770
These things are
in like every game!

407
00:18:24,812 --> 00:18:25,605
[SEIYA]
Nope.

408
00:18:25,646 --> 00:18:27,565
You are really Japanese, right?

409
00:18:27,607 --> 00:18:29,859
Slimes jump at you when they
attack, but they're so weak

410
00:18:29,900 --> 00:18:32,653
that practically anyone can
kill them with just a stick!

411
00:18:32,695 --> 00:18:33,738
So...

412
00:18:33,779 --> 00:18:35,990
[SEIYA growls]

413
00:18:36,032 --> 00:18:37,325
[RISTA gasps]

414
00:18:37,366 --> 00:18:40,703
[RISTA]
Hey, uh, what are you doing?

415
00:18:40,745 --> 00:18:43,956
Now! Atomic Split Slash!

416
00:18:44,957 --> 00:18:50,463
[MONSTER 01A yelling]

417
00:18:50,504 --> 00:18:53,382
[RISTA screams]

418
00:18:53,424 --> 00:18:54,717
Overkill much?

419
00:18:54,759 --> 00:18:57,845
It's just a slime! They're
like, the easiest thing to beat!

420
00:18:57,887 --> 00:18:59,305
[SEIYA]
I'm not done.

421
00:18:59,347 --> 00:19:01,599
I'm afraid it
may still be alive.

422
00:19:01,641 --> 00:19:03,851
Casting Hell's Fire!

423
00:19:05,227 --> 00:19:08,648
[RISTA] The slime is gone,
okay, so just cut it out!

424
00:19:08,689 --> 00:19:11,067
[SEIYA] No, not yet.
There could still be danger!

425
00:19:11,108 --> 00:19:12,109
Huh?

426
00:19:12,151 --> 00:19:14,820
You mean you know more than
two special attacks already?

427
00:19:14,862 --> 00:19:18,991
How about another
Atomic Split Slash attack?

428
00:19:19,033 --> 00:19:22,286
Why use the same attack
twice in a row like that?!

429
00:19:22,328 --> 00:19:23,871
Have another Hell's Fire!

430
00:19:23,913 --> 00:19:26,999
[RISTA] Of course, you'd
have to use that one again!

431
00:19:28,042 --> 00:19:30,503
[RISTA]
He can't be more dead!

432
00:19:30,544 --> 00:19:33,422
Stop! We get it!

433
00:19:33,464 --> 00:19:35,257
Atomic Split...

434
00:19:39,428 --> 00:19:41,639
‐‐[SEIYA] Done.
‐‐[RISTA] That was just a slime.

435
00:19:41,681 --> 00:19:44,809
[RISTA] You vaporized it on
the first atomic whatever.

436
00:19:44,850 --> 00:19:46,352
Always be on guard.

437
00:19:46,394 --> 00:19:48,062
No, not always!

438
00:19:48,104 --> 00:19:49,105
Honestly, Seiya,

439
00:19:49,146 --> 00:19:51,691
I mean you do already have
the Scan ability, right?

440
00:19:51,732 --> 00:19:53,818
Use that to check
the slime's stats.

441
00:19:53,859 --> 00:19:55,903
I did check them, 'kay?

442
00:19:56,904 --> 00:19:59,615
[SEIYA] Its attack and defense
were both in the single digits.

443
00:19:59,657 --> 00:20:01,742
Then why did you
throw everything at it?

444
00:20:01,784 --> 00:20:04,453
There could be more to it
than just the visible data.

445
00:20:04,495 --> 00:20:07,039
Try to have some more
faith in your skills!

446
00:20:07,081 --> 00:20:08,290
Anyway...

447
00:20:08,332 --> 00:20:10,793
...I hope this boosted
your confidence a bit, Seiya.

448
00:20:10,835 --> 00:20:12,586
Look, you have incredible power

449
00:20:12,628 --> 00:20:16,424
and all the equipment that you
would possibly need, so le‐‐

450
00:20:16,465 --> 00:20:17,633
Whoa! What's that?

451
00:20:17,675 --> 00:20:20,636
[MACHINA]
Very impressive swordsmanship!

452
00:20:20,678 --> 00:20:22,805
You're the one, right?

453
00:20:22,847 --> 00:20:25,266
Yes, you must be the one.

454
00:20:25,307 --> 00:20:26,851
Wait, who are you?

455
00:20:26,892 --> 00:20:28,310
[MACHINA] Pleased to
make your acquaintance,

456
00:20:28,352 --> 00:20:30,104
fair goddess and brave hero.

457
00:20:30,146 --> 00:20:31,063
Welcome.

458
00:20:31,105 --> 00:20:34,150
I'm one of Four Heavenly Kings
serving the Demon Lord.

459
00:20:34,191 --> 00:20:36,444
I am known as Chaos Machina!

460
00:20:36,485 --> 00:20:38,904
What? No way, you can't be!

461
00:20:38,946 --> 00:20:41,365
We're not supposed to be
facing a powerful enemy yet!

462
00:20:41,407 --> 00:20:43,743
You sound quite surprised.

463
00:20:43,784 --> 00:20:47,204
Our wise Demon Lord detected
the signs of a hero summoning

464
00:20:47,246 --> 00:20:49,165
before it even happened.

465
00:20:49,206 --> 00:20:51,292
So comically predictable.

466
00:20:51,333 --> 00:20:53,335
Every time a new
hero is summoned,

467
00:20:53,377 --> 00:20:55,671
they head to an area full
of the weakest monsters

468
00:20:55,713 --> 00:20:57,089
to boost their skills,

469
00:20:57,131 --> 00:21:00,176
and when I thought about
where that might be...

470
00:21:00,217 --> 00:21:02,970
...I knew this was the
perfect spot to end you.

471
00:21:03,012 --> 00:21:05,639
Now I see why this is
an S‐Class mission.

472
00:21:05,681 --> 00:21:07,975
I can't use any of
my normal strategies.

473
00:21:08,017 --> 00:21:09,101
[MACHINA]
The Demon Lord has been

474
00:21:09,143 --> 00:21:12,021
vigilantly waiting
for a hero to appear!

475
00:21:12,062 --> 00:21:15,316
I didn't think we needed
to worry, but here we are.

476
00:21:15,357 --> 00:21:18,486
And now that I look at you...

477
00:21:18,527 --> 00:21:20,946
...I can tell you're
something special.

478
00:21:20,988 --> 00:21:22,656
Deep within you
lies the potential

479
00:21:22,698 --> 00:21:25,534
to be an incredibly
powerful foe.

480
00:21:25,576 --> 00:21:27,203
It's too bad.

481
00:21:27,244 --> 00:21:28,579
That won't do.

482
00:21:28,621 --> 00:21:30,247
No, no, no, no, no.

483
00:21:30,289 --> 00:21:32,166
It just won't do at all!

484
00:21:32,208 --> 00:21:35,169
I'll have to end you right now!

485
00:21:36,712 --> 00:21:39,173
[RISTA] Oh, no! I need
to scan her right away!

486
00:21:39,215 --> 00:21:41,425
[RISTA grunts, gasps]

487
00:21:41,467 --> 00:21:42,718
[RISTA] Why are we
going up against someone

488
00:21:42,760 --> 00:21:45,054
this powerful in
the first stage?

489
00:21:46,514 --> 00:21:48,849
How do we get out of this?

490
00:21:48,891 --> 00:21:52,520
I guess we should try to run as
fast as we can, but then what?

491
00:21:52,561 --> 00:21:54,313
What do you think, Seiya?

492
00:21:54,355 --> 00:21:55,231
‐‐[RISTA] Huh?
